$_HOAM_language ['help_pages']['hoam']['new_install'] = '<h1>Welcome to HOAM!</h1><p>Welcome to HOAM, a <a href="https://www.gnu.org/licenses/agpl.html">Free Software</a> package for managing single-family and condominium properties.</p><p>HOAM is intended to give owners living in a neighborhood or condominium building the tools they need to easily administer and operate a property owners association without the need for an outside management company, given a minimum amount of time. Indeed, HOAM is designed specifically to streamline and automate many of the operational tasks of running an HOA.</p><p>There are two options for installing:</p><ol><li><strong>Automatic</strong> Enter the MySQL root username and password, and the installation script will create a database and associated user account for HOAM.</li><li><strong>Manual</strong> This assumes you have already done the manual steps to create and pre-populate the initial HOAM database and user account, and/or are installing the database on a remote server rather than the same system as the web server.</li></ol><p>Please enter in the required database connection information below to begin the install.</p>';
