$_HOAM_language ['help_pages']['website']['cookies_required'] = '<p>We\'re sorry, you will be unable to fully utilize this web site unless you enable cookies in your web browser.</p><p>We use a single cookie (<q>PHPSESSID</q>) that stores a temporary random number &mdash; your <q>Session ID</q> &mdash; which is automatically removed when you close your web browser. This ID is used to remember who you are when you access different portions of the web site such as posting messages in the message board or voting in an online poll.</p><h3>How do I enable cookies?</h3><p>Normally cookies are enabled by default in your web browser. To re-activate cookies please go the <q>Help</q> section on your web browser (Firefox, Internet Explorer, Konqueror, Opera, Safari, et. cetera) and search for cookies. Then, simply follow the instructions to enable cookies.</p><ul><li>[[http://www.mozilla.org/projects/security/pki/psm/help_21/using_priv_help.html | Instructions]] for Firefox or Mozilla</li><li>[[http://www.opera.com/support/tutorials/security/privacy/index.dml | Instructions]] for Opera</li><li>[[http://support.microsoft.com/default.aspx?kbid=260971 | Instructions]] for Internet Explorer.</li></ul><p>Once you have done this, please reload the page, and answer <q>Yes</q> if you are asked whether to accept any cookies. Please note that you may need to exit and restart your web browser for these changes to take place.</p><h3>Other questions</h3><dl><dt>What are cookies?</dt><dd>Cookies are tiny text files that Web sites may store on your computer when you visit certain pages. Cookies cannot harm your computer and do not contain any personal or private information. Your Web browser can be set to accept all cookies, to ask you before accepting a cookie, or to reject all cookies.</dd></dd><dt>I don\'t trust cookies, but I can\'t use your site without them. Why should I trust your cookies?</dt><dd>We need to use cookies to make the resident and homeowner-restricted sections as well as some other functions work. We use a <q>non-persistent</q> cookie, which disappears as soon as you close your browser. If you like, you can enable cookies just for this session, then disable them when you leave the site.</dd></dl><p>If you have any other questions about this website in general or our usage of cookies in particular please send them to the <a href="mailto:%s?subject=Cookie Question">webmaster</a>.</p>';
