$_HOAM_language ['help_popups']['article']['advanced'] = '<h1>Advanced Options</h1><p>There are several additional advanced article configuration options available, however they are not frequently used.</p><p>If you\'re not sure what this is, or whether you should set an option, it\'s probably safe to ignore.</p>';
$_HOAM_language ['help_popups']['article']['allgroups'] = '<h1>All Groups</h1><p>This is a list of all groups that <strong>you</strong> are a member of.</p><p>There may be additional groups configured in the system, but they will not appear if you do not have access to them.</p>';
$_HOAM_language ['help_popups']['article']['article'] = '<h1>Article Content</h1><p>The content of the article.</p><p>The use of both HTML and PHP inside articles is permitted, and used throughout the site. However, this is a known security issue, as <strong>ANY</strong> code embedded will be executed as is, with no checks or warnings.</p><p>If neither a Leadin or Summary is available (see under Advanced Options), the short article list will display a truncated segment of the article.</p>';
$_HOAM_language ['help_popups']['article']['comments'] = '<h1>Comments</h1><p>If set, this flag will allow comments to be posted in reply to the article.</p>';
$_HOAM_language ['help_popups']['article']['draft'] = '<h1>Draft</h1><p>If set, this flag will mark the article as being in draft status, and not ready for posting regardless of the Post Start Date.</p>';
$_HOAM_language ['help_popups']['article']['flag'] = '<h1>Flags</h1><p>There are several flags that may be applied to articles.</p><p>Please see the help for each flag for more information.</p>';
$_HOAM_language ['help_popups']['article']['flags']['comments'] = '<h1>Comments Flag</h1>' . $_HOAM_language ['help_pages']['generic']['no_changes'] . '<p>Whether the article allows comments to be posted to the article. Currently this has no effect.</p>';
$_HOAM_language ['help_popups']['article']['flags']['draft'] = '<h1>Draft Flag</h1>' . $_HOAM_language ['help_pages']['generic']['no_changes'] . '<p>Whether the article is currently in draft status. Currently this has no effect.</p>';
$_HOAM_language ['help_popups']['article']['flags']['redirect'] = '<h1>Redirect Flag</h1>' . $_HOAM_language ['help_pages']['generic']['no_changes'] . '<p>Whether the article is used for redirection to a new URL. This acts the same as an HTTP 302 redirect.</p><p>This is useful if you previously sent out a notification with a misspelling or later decide to change the URL for an article but don\'t want people to be confused.</p><p>It is necessary to enter the full URL, eg: http://www.example.com/new_location/</p>';
$_HOAM_language ['help_popups']['article']['groups'] = '<h1>Groups</h1><p>This is the list of groups allowed to view the article currently being created or edited.</p><p>By default, only a few restricted groups are listed. When an article is ready for publishing, it is recommended to assign the <span class="group_name">Everyone</span> group, which encompasses all other groups on the site.</p><p><strong>Note!</strong> The <span class="group_name">Everyone</span> and <span class="group_name">Anonymous</span> groups are <strong>NOT</strong> identical. Content created for <span class="group_name">Anonymous</span> users will not necessarily be available to members of other groups, including the <span class="group_name">Registered Users</span> group.</p><p><strong>Note!</strong> The <span class="group_name">System Administrators</span> group is always required to be a member. Even if it is removed from this list, it will be automatically added later.</p><p><strong>Note!</strong> If Javascript is not enabled in your web browser, then you must make sure to manually select <em>all</em> of the groups listed; otherwise, any changes made will not take effect.</p>';
$_HOAM_language ['help_popups']['article']['keywords'] = '<h1>Keywords</h1><p>Keywords are used by the search engine to help determine whether the article requested matches the user\'s search request.</p><p>Keywords are also added to the article\'s meta information, which helps with search engine optimization. If no keywords are entered, then the article URI path is used in the meta instead.</p>';
$_HOAM_language ['help_popups']['article']['leadin'] = '<h1>Leadin</h1><p>The Leadin is the introductory section of an article, and is often considered a teaser, enticing the reader to view the entire article. In many cases, a Leadin duplicates the first paragraph of an article.</p><p>If available, the short article list will display the Leadin.</p>';
$_HOAM_language ['help_popups']['article']['minimum_article_length'] = '<h1>Minimum Article Length</h1><p></p>';
$_HOAM_language ['help_popups']['article']['postend'] = '<h1>Post End Date</h1><p>If a date is entered, the article will be removed from display at midnight (12:00am) on the date specified.</p>' . $_HOAM_language ['help_pages']['generic']['date_format'];
$_HOAM_language ['help_popups']['article']['poststart'] = '<h1>Post Start Date</h1><p>If a date is entered, it will not appear for display until midnight (12:00am) on the date specified.</p>' . $_HOAM_language ['help_pages']['generic']['date_format'] . '<p>When combined with the Redirect flag, this becomes a powerful option, allowing scheduling of article changes or moves in advance.</p>';
$_HOAM_language ['help_popups']['article']['redirect'] = '<h1>Redirect</h1><p>If checked, this flag will turn the article into a HTTP/1.1 302 Redirect stub, and the website will redirect users to the location specified.</p><p><strong>NOTE!</strong> Once this article becomes a redirect stub, several changes take affect:<ul><li>All Group Membership settings become moot, and everyone can view the redirect.</li><li>All other settings (Section, Topic, Keywords, Leadin, Summary, Content, etc.) are <strong>erased</strong>.</li></ul></p>';
$_HOAM_language ['help_popups']['article']['redirect_location'] = '<h1>Redirect Location</h1><p>Enter the full URL (including protocol and hostname) to direct the user to, ie: <em>http://www.example.com<wbr/>/new_location/</em> or <em>ftp://ftp.example.com<wbr/>/filename.ext</em></p>';
$_HOAM_language ['help_popups']['article']['root'] = '<h1>Root ID</h1><p>Every article <strong>must</strong> have a Root Article ID.</p><p>Articles are stored in a "tree", with articles branching off of a single root. As each new article is created, it is able to become the root of a new tree.</p>';
$_HOAM_language ['help_popups']['article']['root_id'] = '<h1>Article Root ID</h1>' . $_HOAM_language ['help_pages']['generic']['no_changes'] . '<p>Every article <strong>must</strong> have a Root Article ID.</p><p>Articles are stored in a "tree", with articles branching off of a single root. As each new article is created, it is able to become the root of a new tree.</p><p>The ID you enter here will be the page that HOAM loads for {{WEBSITE_URL}}.</p>';
$_HOAM_language ['help_popups']['article']['summary'] = '<h1>Summary</h1><p>Complimentary to the Leadin, the Summary is a condensed verstion of the article in one or two sentences.</p><p>If a Leadin is not available, the short article list will display the Summary instead.</p>';
$_HOAM_language ['help_popups']['article']['title'] = '<h1>Title</h1><p>The title, or headline of the article.</p><p>The Title must be a minimum of %d characters long.</p>';
$_HOAM_language ['help_popups']['article']['topic'] = '<h1>Topic</h1><p></p>';
$_HOAM_language ['help_popups']['article']['urlname'] = '<h1>URL Name</h1><p>The article URL Name of the article.</p><p>The URL Name must be a minimum of %d characters long.</p><p>The URL Name may only use lower-case alphabetic (a - z), numbers (0 - 9), hyphens (-), and underscores (_).</p>';

$_HOAM_language ['help_popups']['attachment']['description'] = '<h1>Description</h1><p>Description of the file being uploaded.</p><p>The Description is used as the ALT text on images and the TITLE on other file types (such as PDFs).</p>';
$_HOAM_language ['help_popups']['attachment']['file'] = '<h1>File to Upload</h1><p>Select the file to upload.</p>';
$_HOAM_language ['help_popups']['attachment']['maximum_file_size'] = '<h1>Maximum File Size</h1>' . $_HOAM_language ['help_pages']['generic']['new_only'] . '<p>This amount is in Bytes. So, a 1 megabyte file is 1048576.</p><p><strong>Note!</strong> You may also need to modify your <var>php.ini</var> configuration file, see the HOAM <a href="' . HOAM_URL . 'documentation/">documentation</a> for more information.</p>';
$_HOAM_language ['help_popups']['attachment']['minimum_description_length'] = '<h1>Miminum Description Length</h1>' . $_HOAM_language ['help_pages']['generic']['new_only'] . '<p></p>';
$_HOAM_language ['help_popups']['attachment']['preview']['enable'] = '<h1>Enable Attachment Previews</h1><p>Attachments in common image formats (GIF, JPEG, PNG, TIFF) and PDF documents may have small preview images created and shown to the user rather than generic filetype icons.</p><p><strong>Note!</strong> Attachment creation requires the <a href="http://www.imagemagick.org/">ImageMagick <img class="www" src="/hoam/images/external.png" alt="Link to External Site" /></a> libraries as well as <a href="http://www.ghostscript.com/">Ghostscript <img class="www" src="/hoam/images/external.png" alt="Link to External Site" /></a> to be installed on the system.</p><p><strong>Note!</strong> Attachment preview images are not created until the attachment is first viewed. Enabling this option will cause a small performance hit/delay on the initial viewing of an attachment. After the initial viewing, the preview image will be saved for future use.</p>';
$_HOAM_language ['help_popups']['attachment']['preview']['height'] = '<h1>Preview Image Height</h1>' . $_HOAM_language ['help_pages']['generic']['new_only'] . '<p>This setting controls the size of the preview image created and shown.</p><p>If this setting is changed after preview images have already been created, existing preview images will not be recreated but instead are scaled by the web browser to the new size.</p><p>If you want to force the recreation of the preview images, you can click the button below to delete existing preview images.</p>';
$_HOAM_language ['help_popups']['attachment']['preview']['width'] = '<h1>Preview Image Width</h1>' . $_HOAM_language ['help_pages']['generic']['new_only'] . '<p>This setting controls the size of the preview image created and shown.</p><p>If this setting is changed after preview images have already been created, existing preview images will not be recreated but instead are scaled by the web browser to the new size.</p><p>If you want to force the recreation of the preview images, you can click the button below to delete existing preview images.</p>';

$_HOAM_language ['help_popups']['budget']['assessment']['date'] = '<h1>Assessment Date</h1><p>Enter the first date that assessments should be automatically created.</p><p>After thsi initial date, new assessments will be added according to the frequency configured.</p>';
$_HOAM_language ['help_popups']['budget']['assessment']['days_due'] = '<h1>Number of Days After Assessment Payment Due</h1><p>How many days should HOAM wait before sending reminder notices to owners that their assessment is due?</p>';
$_HOAM_language ['help_popups']['budget']['assessment']['days_late'] = '<h1>Number of Days After Assessment Payment Late</h1><p>How many days should HOAM wait before applying a late fee to the owners account for their delinquent assessment payment? This waiting period is typically specified in the governing documents.</p>';
$_HOAM_language ['help_popups']['budget']['assessment']['frequency'] = '<h1>Associaton Assessment Frequency</h1><p>Select how often are assessments due for your association.</p>';
$_HOAM_language ['help_popups']['budget']['assessment']['months_due'] = '<h1>Number of Months After Assessment Payment Due</h1><p>How many months should HOAM wait before sending reminder notices to owners that their assessment is due?</p>';
$_HOAM_language ['help_popups']['budget']['assessment']['months_late'] = '<h1>Number of Months After Assessment Payment Late</h1><p>How many months should HOAM wait before applying a late fee to the owners account for their delinquent assessment payment? This waiting period is typically specified in the governing documents.</p>';
$_HOAM_language ['help_popups']['budget']['assessment']['unit'] = '<h1>Calculate Dues Amount For</h1><p>Select whether assessments are the same for every property, or based on the square footage of the unit (this is only usually ever seen in older condominium associations).</p>';
$_HOAM_language ['help_popups']['budget']['assessment']['time'] = '<h1>Use Days or Months</h1><p>In order for HOAM to calculate whether an assessment is on-time, past-due, or late, it needs to know how soon after an assessment is created that it should begin sending reminder notices and/or applying fees.</p>';

$_HOAM_language ['help_popups']['budget']['category']['description'] = '<h1>Category Description</h1><p>Enter a brief description of the category, such as <q>Legal costs associated with filing liens, such as attorney fees and county clerk filing fees, should go under this category.</q></p>';
$_HOAM_language ['help_popups']['budget']['category']['flags'] = '<h1>Category Flags</h1><p>Various flags that can be set on each category. When entering new charges, and selecting the category for those new charges, the flags shown below will automaticaly be applied to the new charges.</p>';
$_HOAM_language ['help_popups']['budget']['category']['name'] = '<h1>Category Name</h1><p>Enter the name of the new category.</p><p>You may want to review the list of currently existing categories to see if a similar category already exists.</p>';
$_HOAM_language ['help_popups']['budget']['category']['parent'] = '<h1>Category Parent</h1><p>Select the parent catgory (if desired) of this new category.</p><p>This is primarily used for categorizing costs and reporting information.</p><p>When you select an existing parent, the selected budget flags for this new category will be updated to match those of the parent category (flags for parent/child do not need to match, this is simply done for convenience when creating new categories).</p>';
$_HOAM_language ['help_popups']['budget']['category']['track'] = '<h1>Expense Tracking</h1><p>Select whether this category is used for tracking Income or Expenses.</p>';
$_HOAM_language ['help_popups']['budget']['category']['type'] = '<h1>Category Type</h1><p>Select the category type from the selection listed.</p><p>Payments made by homeowners will be applied against certain categories before others, depending on how the system has been configured. For instance, by default, payments will apply to legal costs before being applied to Association Dues.</p>';
$_HOAM_language ['help_popups']['budget']['category']['flag']['interest'] = '<h1>Apply Interest?</h1><p>If checked, the system will automatically calculate interest fees and apply them on any items not paid by the Due Date.</p><p>You will need to verify in your governing documents whether you may charge interest for anything other than regular or special assessments.</p>';
$_HOAM_language ['help_popups']['budget']['category']['flag']['late'] = '<h1>Apply Late Fee?</h1><p>If checked, the system will automatically add a late fee to charges that are after the Late date.</p><p>This should usually be left un-checked, as depending on the jurisdiction only one late fee can legally be charged per invoice and not for each charge.</p>';
$_HOAM_language ['help_popups']['budget']['category']['flag']['sales-tax'] = '<h1>Apply Sales Tax?</h1><p>This should usually be left un-checked.</p><p>If checked, the system will automatically calculate sales tax on this item.</p>';

$_HOAM_language ['help_popups']['budget']['fee']['collection'] = '<h1>Administrative / Collection Fee</h1><p>Enter the optional amount for HOAM to charge owners for sending out delinquent notices. You will want to verify that the association governing documents allow the charging of this fee.</p><p>This is the cost for the administrative labor required to process the assessment collection (printing and mailing notices, making phone calls, researching and verifying owner contact informaton, etc.)</p>';
$_HOAM_language ['help_popups']['budget']['fee']['late'] = '<h1>Late Payment Fee</h1><p>Enter the optional amount for HOAM to charge owners for their payment being past the due date. You will want to verify that the association governing documents allow the charging of this fee.</p><p>This amount is typically specified in the governing documents for the association.</p>';
$_HOAM_language ['help_popups']['budget']['fee']['returned'] = '<h1>Returned Payment Fee</h1><p>Enter the optional amount for HOAM to charge owners if their payment cannot be processed for any reason (eg, a check bounces, payment is removed via a chargeback from the financial institution, etc.) You will want to verify that the association governing documents allow the charging of this fee.</p><p>This amount may be specified in the governing documents for the association.</p>';

